üìñ The Story of Chess

The Chess flows through the Thames & S. Chilterns catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 10 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 5,355 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 673 identified species and 261 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Chess shows above average for diversity, ranking #5 of 10 rivers. The river supports 14 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Eurasian otter, Water vole) and invasive species requiring management attention.
